Defendant Heather M Bukouras in court with attorney Joan B Broughton.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count1  Court finds defendant guilty.

The Court Orders the Following:
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of: 60 Days Huber (Credit -0) HUBER WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.


Term of Probation: 1Years
Conditions of Probation:
-Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
-No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
-Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
-Inform agent of all prescriptions;
-Sign Medical Release for Agent;
-Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
-Maintain/Obtain full time activity
-Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge
-20 hours of community service to be completed during first 10 months of probation. 

Costs: $ 243.00
DNA Surcharge:  $200.00
(To to be paid in 90 days and/or 52 hours of community service to be completed within 90 days. Court must receive notice of completion prior to due date.  Failure to pay or do community service 5 days jail for contempt for non-compliance with court order).
